text: "One" is a 1968 song by Harry Nilsson and it was taken from his third studio album Aerial Ballet. It was covered by Three Dog Night for their debut studio Three Dog Night. It went to number 5 in the United States, number 4 in Canada and number 16 in New Zealand. The John Farnham version made number 4 in Australia in 1969. == References == Category:1968 songs Category:Chamber pop songs Category:Harry Nilsson songs Category:Three Dog Night songs Category:John Farnham songs Category:Filter (band) songs
